description:
&lt;p&gt;Basildon Hospital is the Main District General Hospital for South West Essex and operates from two sites, Basildon University Hospital and Orsett Hospital. We primarily serve the 405,800 population of South-West Essex covering Basildon and Thurrock, together with parts of Brentwood and Castle Point. Basildon Hospital is situated in the town of Basildon and provides acute hospital services for the people of Basildon and Thurrock some of Brentwood and surrounding areas.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Basildon and Thurrock Theatre department has 14 operating theatres, 4 Recovery areas and is a friendly, busy and dynamic Department which operates 24 hours per day 365 days per year and provides a high quality, safe &amp; effective service to all patients who undergo a surgical procedure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to join our Theatres Department for Operating Department Practitioners/ Anaesthetic nurses. Due to service expansion in Theatres we are looking for dynamic, flexible and highly motivated individuals who enjoy working in a team and are a seeking a new opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Individuals will be highly motivated, pro-active team players who possess excellent communication skills. A flexible approach to working is also essential.&lt;br /&gt;We cover a variety of surgery which includes;;&lt;br /&gt;Breast Surgery, Vascular Surgery, Obstetrics, Head and Neck, Urology, general open and Laparoscopic surgery, colo-rectal and ENT, and a new developed MSK service and CEPOD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an opportunity for joint working with the Essex Cardio-thoracic tertiary Centre which is based on the Basildon site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We also provide a General emergency and obstetric emergency service. As part of the service you will be required to support emergencies and provide on-call cover.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We also provide a general emergency and obstetric emergency service. As part of the service you will be required to support emergencies and provide on-call cover.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have close links with Anglia Ruskin University, including supporting pre-registration students of Operating Department Practice Dip HE through their programme of study.&lt;br /&gt;Our recent CQC inspection found us to be ‘providing services that were safe, effective, responsive caring and well-led’.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you think you have something special to offer and want to be part of a patient focused team providing quality care we would welcome your application.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Informal visits are welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Denise Archer- Theatre Manager on 01268 524 900 Extension 4937 &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
